1. BigDecimal represents numbers with an exact precision, while doubles have certain precision. 
When dealing with money, precision is a necessity, so using BigDecimal is better practice. 

2. (1) In the catch block, do not leave it empty or return null. Report the cause of the error
(2) Declare the specific checked exception that your method can throw.
(3) Throw early catch late - more likely to throw in the low-level methods. Wait until you have all the information to handle properly.